-x-hxtmnb: 0.0137em;">8:29 am</span></div></div><div class="_ak8j"><div class="_ak8k"><span class="x78zum5 x1cy8zhl" title="‪Project Guidelines for Students

1) Do Not Start the Project in SkillWallet
Students should not start the project in the SkillWallet portal. The projects listed there are only for reference to check the project titles and descriptions shared in the documents.

2) Use the Appropriate External Platform
Students must complete the project on the external platform related to the technology. Examples:
ServiceNow Projects – Use the ServiceNow Instance
Salesforce Projects – Use the Salesforce Platform
MongoDB Projects – Use VS Code
Gen AI with Google Projects – Use Google Colab
Agentic AI Application Developer (IBM) – Use Google Colab

3) Follow the Project Development Recordings
Students should watch the project development recording sessions and complete the project step-by-step by following the instructions shown in the recordings.

4) Download the Recording if It Does Not Play
If the recordings are not playing online, students can use the download option and watch the recording offline.

5) Use the Shared Project Documents
The project documents drive link has already been shared. Students should refer to these documents to understand the step-by-step process of the project.

6) Understanding Milestones

A Milestone in the project represents a Task.
Each Task contains Activities, which are the steps that need to be completed for that task.

7) Technical Queries
If students face any technical issues or errors, they can:
Post their query in the Telegram group, or
Contact the trainer directly.

8) Uploading the Project to GitHub
After completing the project, students must upload the project files to GitHub. The following items must be uploaded:
Coding Files (if the project contains code)
Project Document – Students must create their own project summary document explaining the project.

9) Demo Video Submission
Once the project is fully completed, students must record a demo video by screen recording their project and explaining the project workflow and implementation.

10) Share Links with Faculty
After completing the above steps, students must share with the faculty:
GitHub Repository Link
Demo Video Link

11) Where to Upload the Files

Project files should be uploaded to GitHub.
Demo video should be uploaded to Google Drive.
Students do not need to submit the files anywhere else.

12) Faculty Submission in Portal
Faculty members will submit the GitHub link and Demo Video link in the project portal, where team formation and project assignment were done.

13) Team Project Submission

This is a team project.
Only one team member can upload the project to GitHub and upload the demo video to Google Drive.
The same links can then be shared with the faculty.‬"><div class="x1c4vz4f x3nfvp2 xuce83p x1bft6iq x1i7k8ik xq9mrsl x6s0dn4"><div class="x78zum5"><span dir="auto" class="x1rg5ohu _ao3e" style="min-height: 0px;">Monika Clg Frnd</span></div></div><span>:&nbsp;</span><span dir="ltr" class="x1iyjqo2 x6ikm8r x10wlt62 x1n2onr6 xlyipyv xuxw1ft x1rg5ohu _ao3e" style="min-height: 0px;">Project Guidelines for Students

